the plots have no equal my mother turned me on to this and it has been fun.. a pleasure to watch , not only for the monk 's character ( worth the price alone ) , but for the ingenious plots . check the airport episode for a woody allen , in an stopped elevator , with a life insurance agent ( season 2 : maid episode , season 3 : 2yr old boy episode ) . do yourself a favor and escape into a fun plotted twist of puzzlements , laughter , and of course : fitting the last pieces into a place with the ahhh ! ! of satisfaction . note some episodes better than others